answer_text: I'm a little confused on the "great confidence" labeling.  You say highlight the relevant part which is a bit ambiguous in this case. Am I just quoting the words that indicate great confidence (like "rest assured" here) or the whole  claim?  One would expect a White House Physician to be a reliable source and say things that are justified, but this whole administration lied on a constant basis. How are we supposed to deal with that?  I realize that's a slippery political slope.  An expectation can be justified due to professional experience (which might be assumed.) Are  you asking if the text provides justification?   Because here the Doctor didn't reveal reasons for their expectation.
